        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "A bit more context from debugging:\r\n\r\nLualine is not required to hit the redraw path. A single statusline redraw is enough:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.defer_fn(function()\r\n  vim.cmd('redrawstatus')\r\nend, 5000)\r\n```\r\n\r\nType a command long enough to wrap and leave the cursor at column 0 of a wrapped line. When redrawstatus executes, the wrapped command line is redrawn once.\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n```\r\n: A very long line that will repeat once after \"redrawstatus\" is executed\r\n: A very long line that will repeat once after \"redrawstatus\" is executed\r\n[]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis does not loop by itself, but is the same redraw path that lualine repeatedly exercises.",
            "created_at": "2026-06-16T14:05:13Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40240#issuecomment-4719626964",
            "id": 4719626964,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/40240",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM8AAAABGU_K1A",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
            "reactions": {
