        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Side note from debugging: redrawing_cmdline looks more like an in-progress transaction flag, while cmdline_was_last_drawn is used as an externally observed state. The assignment between them feels a little surprising, but removing it breaks an older test, so there is some dependency on the current behavior that I haven't fully traced.\r\n\r\nThe current patch doesn't change that behavior; I'm just leaving this note because I ended up spending quite a bit of time looking at the interaction between the two while investigating the redraw loop.",
